title: Toyo Ito pavilion

tags.title: architecture - Do not use this category

description: Believe it or not, this is the Toyo-Ito designed pavilion that was the Serpentine Gallery's summer pavilion back in 2002 (NB the Serpentine gallery, in Hyde Park, commissions an architecturally innovative building every year - which is open to the public for free).  After a summer as a coffee shop the pavilion moved round the world before eventually settling here as the on-site marketing suite for the company developing the Battersea Power Station project.  You can't see much from the ground unless the power station is having an open day, as it's behind a large wall - but it's quite distinctive from the air.  There's a ground level photo on the Wikipedia page.

title: The Parent Trap (1998) - Filming Location
description:
The Parent Trap is a 1998 remake of 1961's family film of the same name. It stars Dennis Quaid and Natasha Richardson as Nick Parker and Elizabeth James, a couple who divorce soon after marrying, and Lindsay Lohan in a double role as their twin daughters Hallie and Annie, who are accidentally reunited after being separated at birth.

This location was used as the James's residence.
